  "summary": "Want to the green book to craft Soul Lanterns but it did nothing",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "I want to the green book in the crafting table and click on the Soul Lantern. and it didn t show up how to make the Soul Lantern. n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Open Minecraft and create a new Creative world or load an existing one.\n2. Ensure you have access to the crafting table and the recipe book feature.\n3. Gather the required items to craft a Soul Lantern: 1 Soul Torch and 8 Iron Nuggets. \n4. Place the crafting table on the ground and right-click to open the crafting interface.\n5. Click on the green recipe book icon to open the recipe book.\n6. In the recipe book, locate the section for crafting items.\n7. Attempt to find the Soul Lantern recipe by scrolling through the available recipes or using the search function.\n8. If the Soul Lantern recipe does not appear, attempt to click on the Soul Lantern icon if visible within the recipe book.\n9. Confirm that the recipe for the Soul Lantern does not display in the crafting table interface, despite having the necessary items in your inventory.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Version 1.21.8",
  "Observed Behavior": "When attempting to use the recipe book (green book) in the crafting table to craft a Soul Lantern, the expected recipe does not appear. The player has opened the crafting table interface, clicked on the green book icon to access the recipe book, and selected the Soul Lantern item. However, instead of displaying the crafting recipe, which should include 1 Soul Torch and 8 Iron Nuggets, the recipe book fails to show any information or crafting instructions for the Soul Lantern. This issue prevents players from easily accessing and utilizing the crafting recipe for Soul Lanterns, which are essential for lighting and aesthetic purposes in the game. The recipe should be available as long as the player has the required materials in their inventory.",
  "Expected Behavior": "When using the knowledge book to craft a Soul Lantern, the expected behavior is that the crafting interface should display the recipe for the Soul Lantern once the player selects it. The recipe should indicate that a Soul Lantern can be crafted using 1 Soul Torch and 8 Iron Nuggets, arranged in the crafting grid. Upon successfully placing the correct materials in the crafting table, the Soul Lantern should appear as a craftable item, allowing the player to create it. If the player has not yet unlocked the recipe for the Soul Lantern, the crafting interface should not display it, and the player should be informed that they need to obtain the recipe first, which can be done through gameplay mechanics such as finding the item or trading with villagers.",
